🎮 Python Rock–Paper–Scissors Game

A simple command-line Rock–Paper–Scissors game built with Python where a user plays against the computer. The computer randomly selects its move, and the program determines the winner based on classic game rules.

This project is beginner-friendly and demonstrates the use of Python basics such as user input, conditional statements, lists, and the random module.

📌 Features

Play Rock–Paper–Scissors against the computer

Computer move is generated randomly

Displays the computer's choice

Announces whether the player wins, loses, or draws

Simple command-line interface

🛠 Technologies Used

Python 3

Random module

